					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Kimber -<br />
<br />
not sure the New England style needs a lot of "flavor melding" time - as opposed to the Manhattan style which needs to extract/blend the leafy herbs and vegetable.<br />
<br />
I should think a hour, perhaps two is max. benefit.  depending on the potato you use (hi/lo starch, there's a debate...) making it too far ahead and holding it could result in unintentional thickening as a starchy potato breaks down.</div>
