<br />
in a home kitchen, you'll probably use something like a stock pot.  the problem with one huge batch is a small heating area (the pot bottom) to a tall volume.  even with stirring I would not expect an even heating throughout the pot - given it's a something viscous mix.<br />
<br />
two large diameter pots would be my approach . . .</div>
