					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">try russets for the chowder.<br />
<br />
white potatoes are often called "all purpose" - they range in the middle regarding starch<br />
<br />
reds, fingerlings, yukons are low starch.<br />
<br />
juice from the clam can - that works!&lt;g&gt;<br />
<br />
our markets (sometimes) have fresh chopped clams in a container.  worth a try if you find them!</div>
