<br />
I have been making a version of chowder for years that my family loves.<br />
I always make a huge potful because they eat it for breakfast and lunch the next day.<br />
<br />
Since our family rarely goes by breakfast conventions, it is rather sweet to see them eat and enjoy huge bowlsful of it the next day and ignore other food.<br />
<br />
What is a standby menu with the chowder is cornbread or a whole grain quick bread, and an apple crisp for dessert, no ice cream or whipped cream.</div>
