					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On October 22, 2011 at 07:02 PM, Dilbert said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">... just everything x6<br />
<br />
bottom line yes, recipes are usually flexible to minor changes in proportions  _except_ <br />
<br />
seasonings - some are "stronger" than others and less than x6 will work - a minor "generality" in this case as the recipe is just salt&amp;pepper<br />
<br />
"thickening" - one single huge pot is is going to cook differently - in particular the amount of starch coming out of the potatoes - so don't put in all the x6 liquids at one crack - hold off to see how it thickens up and be prepared to add more or less liquid than the x6 math indicates.</div>
					<hr size="1" noshade />
				
